<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/oblarg/48/161674_2.png" class="avatar"><a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/in-need-of-working-yagsl-swerve-code/492104/14">In Need of Working YAGSL Swerve Code</a></div>
<blockquote>
<p>If you don’t know what signals to trace, spend some time reading the implementation (including inside of <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span> itself) and try to write down a list of places where the signals <em>could</em> be different from what you expect. Then, log the runtime state of your program and see where the program behavior is diverging from your expectation. There are no shortcuts, and there is no alternative route.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>I would personally recommend trying to get a simpler drive-to-pose command working with <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controllers for X, Y, and theta to create a ChassisSpeeds and pass it to SwerveRequest.ApplyFieldSpeeds. Then once you have that working, try adding more complex features from the code you currently have, like using a ProfiledPIDController and controlling the distance rather than X/Y.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":2,"updated_at":"2025-03-08T02:57:12.840Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":12,"reads":48,"readers_count":47,"score":84.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":494697,"topic_slug":"help-with-aligning-to-a-pose-with-ctre-swerve","display_username":"Kabir","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/in-need-of-working-yagsl-swerve-code/492104/14","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"In Need of Working YAGSL Swerve Code","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57470,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2724 programmer"},"post_url":"/t/help-with-aligning-to-a-pose-with-ctre-swerve/494697/2","custom_user_title":"2724 programmer","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}],"stream